name: Two Tacos
description: Sure, one is nice. But do you know what’s better? Two. Two crunchy tacos with American cheese, shredded lettuce, and taco sauce. Because two will always be greater than one. Who knew math could be so mouth-watering? Oh, right. We did.

name: Seasoned Curly Fries
description: These Curly Fries are seasoned, alright. Seasoned veterans. They’ve been around the block—gathering deliciousness and flavor from all over. So, they know how to make your mouth water. And your tastebuds do their secret handshake.

name: Chicken Sandwich
description: Chicken Sandwich, meet mouth. Mouth, meet Chicken Sandwich—made with a breaded chicken patty, real mayonnaise, and lettuce, all on a regular bun. You two will get along just fine. Just fine, indeed.

name: French Fries
description: Most French fries in the world don’t deserve their own description, but Jack’s do. Because these lightly salted, real potatoes are fried to crispy perfection and served hot and salty. They’re just that tasty.

name: Chicken Nuggets
description: One man’s all-white meat chicken nuggets are another man’s…well, nothing. Because that first man ate all of that crispy chicken amazingness. Next time, get your own, second man.

name: Jack's Spicy Chicken Sandwich
description: Spicy crispy all-white meat chicken with fresh sliced tomato, lettuce and real mayonnaise all on a buttery bakery bun.

name: Stuffed Jalapeños
description: Where most see jalapeños, Jack sees opportunity. To bread ‘em and fill ‘em with melted cheeses. Yes, plural. And, if things get too hot, there’s tasty buttermilk ranch dipping sauce to cool down. Mmhmm. Jack’s got your back. And your stomach.

name: Chicken Nuggets (10pc)
description: All-white meat chicken nuggets with choice of dipping sauce

name: Mini Churros (5pc)
description: Topped with cinnamon and pure cane sugar

name: Breakfast Jack
description: The name speaks for itself. This is breakfast, Jack-style. Think ham, a freshly cracked egg, and American cheese—all on a bun. Now, try to think of something else. That’s right. You can’t.

name: Jumbo Breakfast Platter
description: Breakfast doesn’t come shaped in a bar. Or in a fancy juice. Real breakfast is served on a platter—a jumbo platter with tasty scrambled eggs, hash browns, eight mini pancakes, and your choice of country grilled sausage or three slices of bacon. Checkmate, fancy juice.

name: Ultimate Breakfast Sandwich
description: So, ultimate, huh? Are two freshly cracked eggs ultimate? Maybe. Two slices of American cheese? Possibly. How about two slices of ham and bacon? Potentially. Okay, then what about all of the above on a buttery bakery bun? Oh, yes. Definitely. That’s textbook ultimate. That’s a textbook you want to eat.

name: Extreme Sausage Sandwich
description: When Jack put a sausage patty, American cheese and a freshly cracked egg on a buttery bakery bun, people went nuts. And then when Jack doubled the sausage and cheese, search parties were organized. Because people lost their minds.

name: Loaded Breakfast Sandwich
description: When a breakfast sandwich has freshly cracked eggs, hickory smoked bacon, ham, sausage, melted American cheese, and toasted sourdough bread, it’s just not a breakfast sandwich—it’s the Loaded Breakfast Sandwich. Which means you wouldn’t need to eat anything else. Maybe ever.

name: Sausage, Egg & Cheese Biscuit
description: Four words: Sausage. Egg. Cheese. Biscuit. Yeah, finally, you’ll want to eat your words. Because this buttermilk biscuit is topped with a freshly cracked egg, American cheese and sausage. Scratch that, it’s one word: Incredible.

name: Bacon, Egg & Cheese Biscuit
description: Four words: Bacon Egg. Cheese. Biscuit. Yeah, finally, you’ll want to eat your words. Because this buttermilk biscuit is topped with a freshly cracked egg, American cheese and bacon. Scratch that, it’s one word: Incredible.

name: Meat Lovers Burrito
description: Favorite fruit? Meat. Favorite veggie? Meat. Favorite burrito? This one. It’s got bacon, sausage, and ham—plus, scrambled eggs and cheddar cheese. And it’s all wrapped in a warm flour tortilla with a side of fire roasted salsa. Now that’s a food pyramid you can get behind.

name: Grande Sausage Burrito
description: Your mouth better do some push-ups. Because this is a whole lot of burrito with sausage, scrambled eggs, hash browns, bacon crumbles, and shredded cheddar cheese. Plus, cheddar cheese sauce and creamy Sriracha sauce. And it’s all wrapped in a warm flour tortilla—with a side of fire roasted salsa. Phew. That was a workout just saying all of that.

name: Sausage Croissant
description: When Jack put sausage, a freshly cracked egg and American cheese on a buttery croissant, it earned the coveted title: “the sausage, freshly cracked egg and American cheese buttery croissant.” But that wouldn’t fit on the menu. Or anywhere. Hence, the shorthand.

name: Supreme Croissant
description: This breakfast croissant is more than good. Heck, it’s more than great. This flaky piece of heaven is supreme. Because it’s got grilled bacon, ham, a freshly cracked egg, and American cheese. And when you take a bite, you’re supreme, too. Those are the rules.

name: Supreme Croissant Combo
description: This breakfast croissant is more than good. Heck, it’s more than great. This flaky piece of heaven is supreme. name: Spicy Sriracha Burger
description: Bring the heat. Directly to your mouth. This inferno has it all—100% beef, hickory smoked bacon, sliced jalapeños, Swiss-style cheese, cool shredded lettuce, and fresh sliced tomatoes with spicy, creamy sriracha sauce, all on Jack’s signature toasty sourdough bread. Give your tastebuds a pep talk now, before it’s too late.

name: Bacon Ultimate Cheeseburger
description: How do you make an Ultimate Cheeseburger—with two beef patties, American and Swiss-style cheese, real mayonnaise, mustard, ketchup, all on a buttery bakery bun—even more ultimate? You add three slices of bacon. You read that correctly. Three. Whoever coined “three’s a crowd” has obviously never had this burger.

name: Ultimate Cheeseburger
description: Can a cheeseburger change the world? Nah. Don’t be silly. But an Ultimate Cheeseburger? With two beef patties, American and Swiss-style cheeses, real mayonnaise, mustard, and ketchup on a buttery bakery bun? That can change the world, alright. And maybe Mars. And perhaps that planet with the cool rings around it.

name: Double Jack
description: This isn’t just a burger. This is a Declaration of Delicious. Two juicy, 100% beef patties with American cheese, fresh sliced tomatoes, hand leafed lettuce, and real mayonnaise—all on a buttery bakery bun. Yeah, Great Britain wishes they could get their hands on this amazing piece of America.

name: Jumbo Jack Cheeseburger
description: This is the cheeseburger other cheeseburgers have posters of in their bedrooms. A 100% beef patty topped with two slices of American cheese, lettuce, tomato, pickles, chopped onions, real mayonnaise, and ketchup on a Buttery Bakery Bun. Now, you want a poster too, huh?

name: Sourdough Jack
description: You claim you’re not hungry, but that’s before you read about a 100% beef patty topped with bacon, tomato, Swiss-style cheese, real mayonnaise, and ketchup—all on toasted sourdough bread. One more time for emphasis. Toasted. Sourdough. Bread. See? Now you’re hungry.

name: Classic Buttery Jack
description: Melted garlic herb butter on a juicy ¼ lb.* beef patty. Need we say more? Nay. But we will anyway. Because this beautiful burger has all the fixins’—Swiss cheese, ketchup and mayo, iceberg lettuce, and fresh sliced tomatoes, all on a Gourmet Signature Bun. Need we say more? Nay. For real, this time. *Weight before cooking.

name: Bacon & Swiss Buttery Jack
description: Sometimes, a burger comes along that makes other burgers whimper in fear. This is that burger. Because this ¼ lb.* signature beef patty is topped with melted garlic herb butter, hickory smoked bacon, Swiss cheese, and creamy bacon mayo—and it’s all on a gourmet signature bun. Don’t apologize, it’d be weirder if you weren’t drooling right now. *Weight before cooking.

name: Chicken Fajita Pita
description: Warm pita bread means a whole lot of grain—16 grams of whole grains. But wait, it gets better. Because this pita is filled with Flame grilled chicken, shredded cheddar cheese, iceberg lettuce, grilled onions, and tomato. And, if that’s not enough, there’s also side of fire roasted salsa, too. Alright, now that’s definitely enough. Your tastebuds agree.

name: Club Salad
description: There’s no 400 lb. bouncer in this club. But there is a whole lot of Flame grilled or crispy all-white meat chicken, shredded cheddar cheese, grape tomatoes, cucumbers, crumbled bacon pieces, and gourmet seasoned croutons—all on a blend of iceberg and romaine lettuce. Whoa. And this club has a different dress code—creamy ranch dressing. Leave the silk shirt at home.

name: Grilled Chicken Salad
description: Elsewhere, a salad is an afterthought. But not here. Because this one has crispy all-white meat chicken, shredded cheddar cheese, grape tomatoes, cucumbers, carrots, gourmet seasoned croutons and low fat Balsamic dressing—all on a bed of iceberg and romaine lettuce. You won’t be able to get it out of your head. Or your mouth.

name: Southwest Salad
description: Pack your bags because you’re going southwest, my friend. To a salad made with a blend of iceberg and romaine lettuce. And your choice of Flame grilled chicken or crispy all-white meat chicken—along with shredded cheddar cheese, roasted corn, grape tomatoes, black beans, spicy corn sticks and creamy southwest dressing. Actually, forget the bags. Pack a fork.

name: French Fries
description: Most French fries in the world don’t deserve their own description, but Jack’s do. Because these lightly salted, real potatoes are fried to crispy perfection and served hot and salty. They’re just that tasty.

name: Panko Onion Rings
description: True love is not an engagement ring. It’s an onion ring—panko breaded and fried to jaw-dropping perfection. But using an onion ring as an engagement ring? The judge will allow it. Just kidding. There’s not a judge for this type thing. Do whatever your stomach desires.

name: Stuffed Jalapeños

name: Egg Roll
description: It’s what’s on the inside that counts. That goes for you, sure. But it definitely goes for these crispy egg rolls—filled with diced pork, cabbage, celery, carrots, onions, and spices. But don’t forget the outside, where there’s sweet and sour dipping sauce. You can’t go wrong, really.

name: Seasoned Curly Fries
description: These Curly Fries are seasoned, alright. Seasoned veterans. They’ve been around the block—gathering deliciousness and flavor from all over. So, they know how to make your mouth water. And your tastebuds do their secret handshake.

name: Bacon Cheddar Potato Wedges
description: It doesn’t get any better than golden brown potato wedges. Well, unless you add melted cheddar cheese sauce, shredded cheddar cheese, and diced bacon bits. Which is exactly what we did. Microphone, consider yourself dropped.

name: Two Tacos
description: Sure, one is nice. But do you know what’s better? Two. Two crunchy tacos with American cheese, shredded lettuce, and taco sauce. Because two will always be greater than one. Who knew math could be so mouth-watering? Oh, right. We did.

name: Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger
description: You ever call something “junior,” ironically? Well, if you haven’t, you’re about to. Because this Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger is a 100% beef patty topped with hickory smoked bacon, American cheese, real mayonnaise and ketchup. And now you have a “junior” appetite. See what we did there?

name: Jr. Jumbo Jack
description: Anywhere else this Jr. Jack would be senior. Because there is nothing junior about this honest-to-goodness beef patty topped with tomato, pickle, lettuce, and chopped onions—with the just-right amount of ketchup and real mayonnaise. But here? It’s got some growing up to do.

name: Jumbo Jack
description: When you pick up the Jumbo Jack—made with a 100% beef patty topped with hand leafed lettuce, tomato, pickles, chopped onions, and real mayonnaise on a buttery bakery bun—your arms will tremble. And your mouth will open. It’s the delicious type of workout.
